		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> RotE TR Contest- orgyins winner 2k2<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.62)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=223'>michael "Deck" Gemme</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=223&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> July 15, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Wow.  Where the f to start? Well&#8230; last time you read one of these, I had just earned my bye into the day-two tournament to be held at Deciphercon by placing second at my regional (Coruscant) by one differential; beating the likes of Chris Terwilliger, Chris Prascak and Johnny Chu.  It&#39;s been some time since then, and you really need to be brought up to speed.<br />
<br />
With my performance at regionals, my rating was boosted to a staggering 2027.  I&#39;ve played in two tournaments since regionals (not including the Origins open), the NYC mini-con, where I went 4-2 and a random Providence tournament where I went 3-3 because I couldn&#39;t play my light deck well.  News spread of the Dantooine regional with 57 attendees, the return of the game was upon us; vicious rumors about Decipher regaining the rights to StarWars again&#8230; crazy hiney siht my friends&#8230; I don&#39;t know what turn the game will take, I know that it will continue to surge towards the October 31st date of DecipherCon, where 5,000 dollars will be at stake for the greatest CCG that was ever created, and based on what I&#39;ve seen, heard and read&#8230; this game is not dead; its not the same game, but the game itself has not died.  To follow is the story of the game as now, not a game where Canadians sit at the top looking down on the lowly Americans, not a game where you&#39;re not good if you play outside of Southern California, and not a game where the highest rated players are the only contenders to deal with.  The game is in the hands of the ones that care about it.  The story surrounding it? Well that involves corruption, triumph, genius, obsession, and heavy boozing.  And it starts in mid-June with a monumental trip to Boston College, a bar called the tap, and a Russian chick named Olga.<br />
<br />
I have a long work week.  I work forty hours as a pool director at a summer camp, then on Friday, I go from one job to the other, work another 6 hours lifeguarding at a hotel pool.  I get Saturdays off and then I work Sunday at the hotel again before my 40 hour camp week starts again.  One of my best friends from highschool Matt, who goes to school with Justin and has an apartment in his town, is turning 21 so obviously I have to go into the city and celebrate.  Only I have to work until 10, so I get out of work and jet to Boston and meet up with Justin so we can go meet up with my friends from highschool at a bar downtown.  Justin and I head over to his buddies&#39; house and do some shots and we&#39;re like SHOTS? Because somewhere Justin had the idea that you could get a girl at a bar with simply saying shots.. more on how that failed us later.  <br />
<br />
We take the T downtown and im sitting on the train and frigging this Indian guy with a baby plops down right next to me and im trapped, nowhere to move for about a half hour, totally segregated from Justin and his boys, and they&#39;re laughing at me, so im trying not to laugh wicked hard at 1. the Indian guy with a cute baby that everyone is looking at and noticing how I am trapped, and 2. the red headed chick across the car whose nipple is showing as her breasts completely pop out of her shirt.  Finally we get downtown, I leap over the Indian baby and we head to a bar called The Tap (we were going to go to cheers, but my friend dan&#39;s girlfriend Jackie got her id taken away, and had to buy it back for 100 bucks.. then this bar the purple shamrock didn&#39;t accept mass liquor id&#39;s when my friend sean doesn&#39;t have his liscense so we ended up at the tap) and we just start drinking.  Buying mad beers for everyone, doing lots of shots with my boy matt (one of which was jagr, goldschager and rumplemints) which is the grosses concoction of alcohol ever created.  I love how I just spelled three consecutive boozes completely and utterly incorrect.  Anyways, now to olga.  Olga is this Russian chick&#8230; who is ridiculously hot.  And Justin pointed her out when he got there mentioning how he wanted her, all his friends wanted her, my friend matt told me he wanted her and has been working on her for years&#8230; well I proceded to get extremely shtifaced and start dancing/making out with her on the dance floor for about say 2 hours straight causing a complete spectical of myself&#8230; my friend matt gets pissed, Justin is completely enamored, and all in all I just am totally into frenching an incredibly gorgeous girl with a Russian accent.  She tells me that her roommate is gone for the weekend and that I should go back to her place with her.  Who is mike gemme to refuse a lady.. let alone one that is actually gorgeous.  I go back to her place, we hook up, no latex=no sex (im no matt lush) but we throw hooks and she sleeps naked on top of me for the entire night kissing my body and shti and my hand does not remove itself from her perfect skin, and is centrally focused on the touching of her buttox.  At 330 I cant get ahold of Justin to go back because he as my car key so that I wouldn&#39;t drive but at the same time who knows where he is and I might need to get home in the morning.. still I have to frigging call into work the next day because I was scheduled at two of my jobs (one that I would eventually quit for the camp, but the camp hadn&#39;t started yet so I accidentally scheduled myself at two pools)&#8230; so I go online to get the phone number of the hotel and make a call that goes something like this:<br />
<br />
Night Manager: Hello?<br />
Me: Hi this is mike the morning guard, I cant make it in.. im actually in boston at brigham and women&#39;s hospital getting my stomach pumped&#8230; yeah I got food poisoning.  Have you ever gotten your stomach pumped? Oh yeah it&#39;s the most god-awful thing you could ever experience.  Yeah I&#39;m in triage.. okay bye.<br />
<br />
Justin would later comment &quot;Once you said triage you had her&quot;<br />
<br />
So around 415 justin calls me up on my cellular telephone and im like dude you have my cell phone, where the F are you&#8230; of course hes on his way down to foxwoods (a casino in Connecticut, which is a good two hours away) and he thinks he&#39;ll make it back on time, but who knows because foxwoods is foxwoods and gambling is gambling and Justin is Justin and I was just extremely worried&#8230; but I hung up the phone and looked at the heap of Russian goodness on top of me and I say &quot;say I have food poisoning in Russian&quot; to whish she spurts out &quot;woiadsllsdk aoiweur;oajdlsfdl&quot; and I pass out.<br />
<br />
