<br />
6(+87)<br />
<br />
Highs: 36 forces with light is huge when youre not playing qmc.<br />
Lows : Absolutely none.<br />
<br />
So this puts me in second behind hayes hunter, who just won with his dark.  This means I have to play my dark senate vs his light.  Justin is completely confident in this match, I however am not.  I freak out, we go put money in my parking meter and I try and get Justin to reassure me of the matchup.  We just threw in an extra aks moe the night before, so we had extra ls senate tech, if you could call it that.  We go back into the hall and im trying not to freak out, and as I sit down I begin to feel confident and I sit next to Justin who is playing eric with his light at the second table spot.  This is phat because kashyyyk represents the top four spots at origins.  Kim takes pictures of the spectacle for us and we begin playing.<br />
<br />
Game 4 my DS senate vs. hayes&#39; light senate<br />
<br />
Well the game starts off good as I get a sick opening hand, 2 senators and a squabble.  I also get ability x3 but I never actually deploy it because I don&#39;t want to invite him to come down to the senate first turn.  Either way, he gets his hand and goes, hey mcclure! And mcclure goes &quot;oh you win&quot; to this eric tells hayes to shut up, which was cool of him to back me up when hayes was showboating.  I put down lott dodd and toonbuck.  He puts down bacta tank.  But in his first turn I forget to get a political effect, and in my second turn I forget to grab a docking bay. I do vote now for four cards and throw down some more senators.  Early on, his like third turn, I have nothing to deploy, he has five cards in hand, I make him drop two which sets him back a ton, and I am in good shape. This is pretty much how the game goes from here on in.  he drops palpatine and obi wan, or palpatine and obi wan and battles, draws low, I lose one from the battle (he starts dtf, I start colo claw so he cant, our ls senate deck my only idea for the deck haha) and I lose a senator as well.  After I lose three I squabble but at this time I have the senate held down.  I get the baron/ship/system combo early but I don&#39;t deploy it stupidly. Finally I do, and then I say go.  He goes probably battles me again.  Now the next turn I am activating and he&#39;s acting all surprised at baron at my system. I say drain four, ping for one, drop two cards and lose four to limited.  9 card loss in a game that looked stalemate.  His jaw drops.  From here on in I start draining as fast as I can and he battles me, I lose a card, sometimes a senator when I don&#39;t subtract from his destiny.  Thing is I always have my senator, I just save it for the drain or whatever I want basically.  Time is getting called soon and he asks me to draw up, but says he will happily draw up.  Hayes got a draw up in game 2, he would again get one in game 5, I told him I want to win origins, he will most likely get the buy.  He draws up when he has few cards left and I get the full win by 20.<br />
8 (+108)<br />
<br />
Highs: Beating hayes when he got a mint start. McClure eating his words.<br />
Highs : Eric and Sokol backing me up when hayes was talking smack.<br />
Lows: The game going to time, holding my space stuff too long.<br />
<br />
So that puts me in the top spot, eric is in second.  So I play eric with my light, which is a tough matchup.  Justin lost to eric&#39;s isb, which again is a tough matchup because eri&#39;c isb is just sick and now I have to play it&#8230; yay<br />
<br />
Game 5 my LS Combat vs. Eric Hai&#39;s ISB Bombers.<br />
<br />
I drop down and hold to my one site, the 3/2.  I get underworld out, I had artoo in my hand.  I put yoda down, anything to get me to activate the most force.  He goes to naboo with jonus and zuckuss, he tried to combat response for baron instead of zuckuss but saber 1 wasn&#39;t there so my han/chewie/falcon becomes obsolete.  He puts mad walkers and guys to his <> dbay on naboo to limit my drain.  I throw artoo, the baragwins, threepio, yoda and obi wan there.  He bombs my site.  he puts his guys inside the walkers, declares his power 14.  I go to space with hcf and move over to coruscfant where he is draining me with a unique sd.  Down comes baron, I draw four destiny with life debt and clear that system.  He moves his walkers over to executor.  I start draining for more.  At one point I try to go to the podrace arena with lando and luke.  He overloads luke at random.  He is draining me for little, and I him for little, we are both retrieving little with his objective and my baragqwins.  He moves his guys back, does not take them out of the walker.he tramples artoo, battles, declares his power 33. which is mad shady.  To my power of very little, I lose everything but a baragwin who I move over to try and control the force loss.  I edge for six but it is too little too late and I am outdrained and beaten by 11 forces.<br />
8(+97)<br />
<br />
Highs: keeping it close in a really bad matchup<br />
Lows : Eric&#39;s imperial walker maneuver more than doubing his power.<br />
<br />
Well Justin wins his game, but I still have the highest diff in the tourney and I am stuck playing the only undefeated person, eric hunter and his ls combat similar to Johnny chu&#39;s.<br />
I go to the bathroom for about the 20384355320328th time that day, and eric gets me a water, as I walk back through the con room I am very angry, like a man with a mission, and I had one, but I was acting like it.  It was confidence boosting.  With my dgma pin secured tightly into the fly of my pants, I sit down for my sixth and final game of the tournament.<br />
<br />
Game 6 my ds senate vs. eric hunters ls combat<br />
<br />
I set up the senate, he puts down tons of icons for me so that in my third turn I activate 17.  in his second turn he put down obi wan to his 2/2 site.  down comes baron to the system and maul to the site, battle, maul strikes, I have you now, draw 4,5,7 and he takes 17 overflow.  I get pissed at myself because I figure he has the houjix and I wasted all my adders, well he doesn&#39;t and takes the 17 forces.  He wins his race the next turn but my coward prevents him from retrieving.  I lose six then spot 6 senators with squabble and get it all exactly back.  I lost my drain cancellor effect early so I cant shut down the malastaire drain with home1, but abilityx3 and my drains and limiteds and things like that are putting him away solidly, I put porn free ta back and when the dust settles I win by 25.<br />
10(+118)<br />
<br />
Highs: I just won my first tournament<br />
Lows : Beating my friend with a huge beatdown<br />
<br />
Here is where the controversy kicks in.  Justin beats brian twigg by 32 because of ungrabbed edges, which puts him at a diff of 102.  hayes diff is 89 which means he has to win by 13.  so instead of calling hayes&#39; game after 60 minutes, eric olson decides to let hayes keep playing because, and I quote &quot;the game matters&quot;  well it mattered for a bunch of other people too.  Letting hayes have 20 extra minutes to get a full win instead of a timed win, put hayes in third place instead of about 6th place, giving him the bye instead of eric hunter.  During the phantom 20 minutes, we tried to appeal to both Andrew howard and eric olson but eric had the final say and we really could do nothing&#8230; which is horrible because origins is the first big tournament that was put in the hands of the players committee and they absolutely f&#39;d it up harder than any tournament I&#39;ve ever been to. Moreso than worlds day 1 in 2k&#8230; more than anything.  No offense to the players, they just should not have been allowed extra time at all.  <br />
<br />
Everyone is all enamored by what happened with hayes game as it was going on and noone really understood the fact that I just won the sanctioned origins tournament. Which is a huge deal with 69 players.. it&#39;s a big tournament!! Finally I convince everyone to be excited for me.  Hayes&#39; game finally ends and he doesn&#39;t win by 13 and its me and Justin h20 desai in the finals.<br />
<br />
The kashyyyk train of dominence finally descended upon the swccg gaming community.<br />
<br />
Two regional runner ups with a sick as dark side senate deck just broke the top two spots at the biggest tourney of the year so far.  And we were pretty happy about it.  Noone really stuck around for the final except for matt sokol, which was cool.  Olson and howard supervised it too.  The Albany guys play some raw deal and everyone else pretty much disappears.  Me and Justin sit down to play, I elect to play dark first, because I basically know it&#39;s a win and know how much I have to lose by in order to win the final, because I doubted that our dark would lose, even if I did beat it last night in a playtesting match.  On to the games.<br />
<br />
Extremely meaningful bonus game #1<br />
My ds senate vs justins wys.<br />
We&#39;ve played this matchup before.  I kick him off a system (kessel) early.  Hes got drains going at some docking bays.  I drop vader to block one, he dies, the drain stays.  I drop maul to tattooine and he starts running around blocking drains.  Vader gets placed out of play when we demonstrate how cool a mirrors out of commission would be when the player gets to choose two cards from the lost pile and picks one to be put out of play.  So byebye vader.  The rest of the game becomes a drain race / senate tech damage race, and without much battling except for han in the falcon to take out my ships, I pull out the win by 14.<br />
<br />
Highs: Well winning the matchup.  Justin knows the deck better than anyone, he built it.<br />
Lows: now I have to beat this nasty senate or try and lose to it by less than 14&#8230;14 is the smallest the deck has ever won by.<br />
Other: This game was phat because mad people took pictures of us playing during it.<br />
<br />
Since Justin and I were playing identical dark decks, I just handed him mine and whipped out my combat deck, we threw down our stuff, shook hands one more time.  And drew hands.<br />
<br />
Justin got a god draw.<br />
<br />
Game 2 my ls combat vs justin&#39;s my justin&#39;s senate with a god draw.<br />
My hand aint that shabby either.  I get artoo down with an extinguisher and a baragwin first turn to try and put pressure on him, but I know that hes got the extra senator to cancel the drain because hell I saw his hand, he showed it to me.  Next turn I get down quigon and I&#39;m pretty set.  I start looping my devices.  He&#39;s limiteds me early&#8230; I lose four cards, one of which, I did it.  Doh!  So I win the race, he squabbles.  From here on in it is a drain race and I cant get any of my lowly space stuff to try and even go at him there, and finally the drains start to get to him as im trying to loop my devices, but sometimes you just cant get the device thing off, if theyre not on top, plus paying four to retrieve two is tough.  I drop yoda to put some more pressure on him, hoping maybe that I can hold off a beatdown til I can snag an obiwan or something, no luck.  Vader comes down, but doesn&#39;t hit and and instead of losing 11 I lose like yoda and four.  I couldn&#39;t get my edge off because I never got obi wan or luke out, and without I did it I retrieved 0 force from anything other than baragwins.  In the end I was trying to track a one to retrieve 2 with nar shadda (whoohoo) but I couldn&#39;t get it done and I ended up losing by 9, which isn&#39;t bad because it catapults me into the winning spot of origins.  <br />
<br />
Yay for school.  My first tournament win just happens to be a 70 man battle royal with 20 2000 rated players and 5 2100s.  not bad.  <br />
<br />
So like I said before, since Justin and I had already gotten byes, they got pushed down to hayes hunter and graham &#39;keep it honest&#39; neal.  And if not for the players committee debacle, then it would&#39;ve gone to eric hunter who came in fifth.  Now a lot of people are asking what I won for winning such a large and historically important tournament.  Heres what I got: a lousy deciphercon2k tshirt with the emperor on it.  A maul with saber foil.  That&#39;s it.  Not even a can of soda.  Not even anything.  Nada.  I just wish decipher gave 2 shtis about this game, even if they don&#39;t have a license, swccg made that company, they could show a little faith since it outsold swtcg last month, and has such a massive cult following.  I dunno, give me some packs of cloud city, mention the tourney on the website.  Anything really, would be appreciated.  Life sucks sometimes in that respect.<br />
<br />
Well after the tournament, we get some cards signed.  Its funny before the final some little kid like 9 was in the bathroom (yikes this story sounds bad aleady) and hes putting his cards into his pockets and im like dude don&#39;t do that to your cards, so I float him a deck protector box, the blue plastic ones that come with the plastics with the little triangles at the bottom.  I dunno, he was a good kid probably and I didn&#39;t want him ruining his lord of the rings cards.  Afterwards when we were doing signings, he came over and gave me some warlord cards (which came free when you registered for the con) but still it was nice of him, and I signed is lotr site 5 and he signed my dark numbers canceller shield.  I didn&#39;t get many cards signed, just my shields, which is phat because noone usually has signed shields, or at least I haven&#39;t seen one, so it was fun.  We went back to the bar, I played some scrabble with kim who wouldn&#39;t play me the previous day, citing &quot;I was up playing with your hiney all night&quot; cricket&#8230;cricket&#8230; tumbleweed&#8230;<br />
Mainly we just do some chilling and drinking, everyone is wicked pipeweeded except for me and Justin.  Kim bought me a shot, four horsemen of the apocalypse&#8230; daniels, beam, quervo and some other dude I cant think of, but it smelled like turpentine.  At about 2-230 we called it a night because we had a wee bit of driving the next day (only 12 hours). <br />
<br />
Oh wait, we also went to a restaurant, me, eric, Justin, the twigs, sokol, aaron kingery.  It was pretty phat bar/restaurant.  Pretty expensive but I treated myself to a chicken parm meal.  We just hung and took pictures and signed some more cards and basically talked about what virtual card I should make.  Ranging anywhere from a new death star to a broken effect you can start with heading for the medical frigate.  The card would compeltey change the game and literally bring balance to the force&#8230; but I&#39;m not going to make it.  I think people will dig the card I make. Its not super good, but it&#39;s a cool fricking idea.<br />
<br />
We got back to the hotel, I completely crashed I was exhausted.  At like 330 I got a phone call on my cell that woke us up but I didn&#39;t get it in time, apparently it was one of my girlfriends from high school drunk.  I still see her from time to time so it wasn&#39;t that weird, but like&#8230; yeah it was cause I see her like twice a year.  I got back to sleep and had the strangest fricking dream ever.  I dreamt I was still with my girlfriend from the last two years and we were still together, like never broken up&#8230; she was pregnant with my kid, and she&#39;d given me aids&#8230; yikes&#8230; only light at the end of THAT tunnel is that at some point I would finally succumb to the aids.<br />
<br />
We get up at like 1030 and we get eric back to the con and pretty much just start driving due east.  We talk a lot about the tournament, the games, the amount of shti that was talked to us over the course of the weekend, especially by McClure and Pete Sordorski.  We discussed the implications of us finishing in the top two, how legit we are (pretty legit) and the shady dealings of the players committee.  We do a few more six degrees of Kevin bacon.  We do the two degrees of mike gemme connecting me to every player in the top ten within two moves, except for the guy from spain, noone I&#39;ve beaten has played that kid as far as I know, but 9/10 aint bad.  We actually get kind of lost and head all the way to Cleveland and we get to see browns stadium and the Indians stadium, which is kind of cool.  We find I-90 which is strange, because we&#39;re like &quot;hey we got one of those in Mass, its called the Mass Pike&quot; figuring it&#39;s the same one, we jump on that and ride it all the way back to Worcester.  Stopping only to change drivers once and then again in Amstergosh darnitY, the city of a thousand banks.  Where I stayed when I was 13 and went to the baseball hall of fame with my dad and his friend danny. <br />
<br />
Quick sidenote. Im lifeguarding at the hotel I work at, the one that gives me  the discount on my hotels when I go away, and two ppl just got into the hot tub, and theyre like late 30s and making out and the guy is totally feeling the girl up and kissing her breasts&#8230; I am literally 7 feet away from them right now&#8230; yikes.<br />
<br />
Anyways, back to Amsterdam.  We go to this pizzaria and the guy wont let us eat in there even though they don&#39;t close for another half hour, he says they already swept and shti.  So we go sit on my car, by a newspaper, read the worlds worst editorial by some fat guy whose wife is gone for fourth of july weekend.  Podunk newspapers are really so terrible.  We bust out the warlord decks we got for registering as well as the packs we got for it, and we have no idea how to play the game but it seems pretty horrible.  Justin pulled a rare foil which is cool.  My rare was a horse possession. Bill the pony. gosh darnit.  <br />
<br />
We eat our bacon and hamburger pizza, and get back on the road.  We get home around 1130 making it a 12 hour trip including the half hour stop in Amsterdam for pizza.  The first thing we do is check our fantasy teams, which I haven&#39;t all weekend.  Of course mark burhle is on my bench and pitches 7 scoreless.  My last 5 starts when he&#39;s actually in, he&#39;s 0-4 with an era over 4.  gosh darnit.  The second thing we do? We frigging crash.<br />
<br />
Next morning we get up at like 645 so I can take Justin to the airport and get to work so I can talk to the amazingly gorgeous 17 yr old blonde bombshell with green and blue eyes and aljdl;asfalsjfasdj she&#39;s just good.  The long weekend of intercourse and card playing is behind us and we look forward to deciphercon2k2.  wow.  Try typing deciphercon into word and its got a squiggly red line under it.  Type decihpercon2k2&#8230; no line&#8230; its all good.  Weird.  Well I really hope I haven&#39;t forgotten anything.  This thing is only 17 pages single spaced, which aint bad I guess.  I&#39;ve still got props and slops to do.  I think my freedomcon report is longest to date (note 23 single spaced).  So I&#39;m gonna bounce.  Origins winner. What what. <br />
<br />
Maddest Props Imaginable<br />
<br />
Justin H20 Desai for making my decks, being my partner, we won this tournament bro, not just me.  This is huge for us.  The next few months will be insane, whether it be stealing street signs of Olga Av (which is off Belmont street in Worcester) or going to leitrums, screaming &quot;shots&quot; to get girls, or playing an occasional game of cards or an occasional 23 games of scrabble in a row.  I would&#39;ve came in last at this thing without your decks, and we both know that.  So great job, and it&#39;s not over yet.<br />
<br />
